Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.57,0:00:23.24,Default,,0,0,0,,This wasn’t the first health scare with Mum.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.68,0:00:29.68,Default,,0,0,0,,And my brother and sister
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.68,0:00:31.85,Default,,0,0,0,,were always quick to help out.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.00,0:00:54.50,Default,,0,0,0,,But this time was different.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.31,0:01:06.22,Default,,0,0,0,,She’d be here for at least another week\Nand then more long-term care.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.85,0:01:13.49,Default,,0,0,0,,We just weren’t prepared for that.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.93,0:01:26.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I should have accepted\Nmore help when the friends offered.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.30,0:01:29.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I just didn’t want to be a burden.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.94,0:01:33.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Janice understood,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.94,0:01:37.24,Default,,0,0,0,,and she was wondering\Nhow this might affect her Bethel service.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.98,0:01:42.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Terrance wished he lived closer\Nso he could do more.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.95,0:01:47.82,Default,,0,0,0,,We decided to pray, sleep on it,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.82,0:01:50.19,Default,,0,0,0,,and regroup after doing some research.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.92,0:02:24.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I shared the example of Joseph in Genesis 45,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.60,0:02:31.60,Default,,0,0,0,,where he told his father:
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.47,0:02:38.24,Default,,0,0,0,,“You must dwell in the land of Goshen,\Nwhere you will be near me . . .
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.24,0:02:40.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I will supply you with food.”
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.28,0:02:47.75,Default,,0,0,0,,He didn’t let a long distance\Nget in his way of caring for Jacob.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.42,0:02:54.42,Default,,0,0,0,,He took practical steps
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.96,0:02:58.13,Default,,0,0,0,,and made his care a priority.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.24,0:03:09.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Janice and Terrance too found great articles
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.07,0:03:11.64,Default,,0,0,0,,offering solutions
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.64,0:03:15.31,Default,,0,0,0,,such as asking for periodic help,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.49,0:03:26.86,Default,,0,0,0,,making more time to communicate with Mum,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.73,0:03:39.13,Default,,0,0,0,,or even getting a part-time nurse.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.68,0:03:52.52,Default,,0,0,0,,We weren’t prepared\Nfor her situation to change so suddenly,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.85,0:03:59.52,Default,,0,0,0,,but Jehovah is guiding us\Nthrough each new challenge.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.86,0:04:09.56,Default,,0,0,0,,And with his help, we’re honoring Mum,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.63,0:04:14.63,Default,,0,0,0,,making her care our continual priority.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.91,0:04:27.31,Default,,0,0,0,,In this dramatization, we saw one way
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.32,0:04:30.82,Default,,0,0,0,,that a family decided\Nto care for an aging parent.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.82,0:04:35.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, situations will differ\Nfrom one family to the next.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.06,0:04:45.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Each must make a prayerful decision\Nbased on their circumstances.
